The paper deals with the design of incentive mechanisms for computation offloading via device-to-device communication, while taking into account interdependent security risks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), game theory (cs.GT), networked systems (cs.NI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
